Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
Jessop House is situated on the south side of Jessop Avenue to the west of the town centre. The building fronts Jessop Avenue which leads onto St Jamesâ Square and the town centre via Clarence Street. It is a short walk from the local shops and amenities and a 10-minute walk from Cheltenham Spa Rail Station. At the end of Jessop Avenue there is a Waitrose store, petrol station and car park developed by the John Lewis Partnership.

Jessop House is a Grade A office building developed in 2002 over ground and 4 upper floors with an impressive full height reception and a mix of ground level and basement parking.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: Cheltenham is a popular spa town located on the edge of the Cotswolds and is famous for its Regency Architecture. The town benefits from excellent road access to junction 10 & 11 of the M5 via the A40. The A417/419 also provides easy access to Swindon and M4. The building is located in the established office location of St James Square which is less than one mile from Cheltenham Spa Station and a short walk from Cheltenhamâs main amenity offering including a range of bars, restaurants and retail outlets including the well-known Promenade. There is also a large Waitrose supermarket adjacent to the subject property. The property comprises a high-quality office on ground and 4 uppers floors with basement shower and cycle parking facilities. The available accommodation is situated at ground floor.
